&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Liberis Sales Representative, you will be part of a growing team based from our Central and Eastern Europe hub in Munich, and part of an established global Sales team. Your main responsibilities in this role include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The exciting task of supporting our customers in the DACH region&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as a link between our customers and internal teams, working closely with the product and partnerships team to continuously improve our offerings for customers in Central and Eastern Europe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing leads and providing a positive first contact experience for our potential customers through effective consultation; this includes handling incoming calls from interested parties as well as making outbound calls as part of our sales strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working closely with our external partners to ensure a high conversion rate for the leads we receive from them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking responsibility for managing your own customer base through personalized consulting and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Having the opportunity to work on and further develop existing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keeping the Liberis behaviours at the forefront of everything you do!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
